@dev
Initializes the contract and enables public purchasing.
@param owner The owner of the contract. Can be set later with `transferOwnership`.
@param legendCoin_ The address of the LEGEND ERC20 token
@param metadata_ The address of the upgradable metadata contract
@param powerUpCost_ The initial cost in LEGEND to purchase a power up

@notice
Purchase a random Legend Maps Power Up with LEGEND ERC20 tokens.
@dev
Reverts if:
  - Purchasing is currently disabled.
  - Spending LEGEND fails, usually because insufficient balance.
@param amount The amount of power ups to purchase
@return ids The power up IDs minted to the player

@notice
Burn a power up.
@dev
Reverts if:
  - The power up ID is out of bounds (i.e. the power up does not exist).
  - The player does not have enough power ups to burn.
@param id The ID of the power up to burn
@param amount The amount to burn

@notice
Add a new power up to the list of available power ups.
@dev
The power up ID is the index of the power up in the `rarities` array + 1.
The cumulative rarity sum is also increased.
Reverts if:
  - The rarity exceeds the maximum value of uint8.
@param rarity The rarity of the power up, lower is more rare, 0 is not available

@notice
Update the rarity of a power up.
@dev
It does so by updating the rarity in the `rarities` array, and updating the cumulative
rarity sum.
Reverts if:
  - The power up ID is out of bounds (i.e. the power up does not exist)
  - The new rarity exceeds the maximum value of uint8.
@param powerUpId The ID of the power up to update
@param rarity The new rarity of the power up, lower is more rare, 0 is not available

@notice
Remove a power up from the list of available power ups.
@dev
It does so by setting the rarity to zero, and updating the cumulative rarity sum.
Reverts if:
  - The power up ID is out of bounds (i.e. the power up does not exist)
@param powerUpId The ID of the power up to delete

@notice
Sets the metadata contract address
@dev
After updating, you may want to call one of the `refreshMetadata` functions
so that marketplaces can update their metadata.
@param metadataAddress The new address for the metadata contract

@notice
Refresh the metadata for all token IDs
@dev
Uses the ERC1155 URI event in a loop which is not ideal,
but there's no batch event for this with ERC1155. It might be worth
trying `refreshAllMetadata4906` first.

@notice
Refresh the metadata for a specific token ID using EIP4906
@dev
Some marketplaces may support the EIP4906 event for ERC1155 metadata updates,
but it's not guaranteed.
@param id The token ID to refresh

@notice
Refresh the metadata for all token IDs using EIP4906
@dev
This is a workaround for the fact that the ERC1155 URI event does not
support batching. Some marketplaces may support the EIP4906 event for
ERC1155 batch metadata updates, but it's not guaranteed.

